Installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the React/Vite project.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^2.0.1` package using npm
- Package added to dependencies in package.json

### 2. Analytics Component Configuration
Modified `src/App.tsx`:
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the root level of the App component
- Placement ensures analytics tracks all pages (Home, Reader, and Loading states)

### 3. Verification
- ✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
- ✅ Linter passed with no errors (npm run lint)
- ✅ Lock file (package-lock.json) updated correctly

## Implementation Details:

The implementation follows the latest official Vercel Analytics documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):
- Used the framework-specific React import (`@vercel/analytics/react`)
- Placed the Analytics component at the root level of the application
- Component is rendered as a sibling to the main app content, ensuring it loads on every page

## Next Steps:

To activate analytics in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Analytics section in your Vercel project dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate analytics
4. Once deployed and users visit the site, analytics data will be visible in the dashboard

The Analytics component automatically tracks page views and visitor data once the application is deployed to Vercel. No additional configuration is required for basic analytics tracking.
